4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT TRANSFERRING THE WORKERS' COMPENSATION JUDGE
5 FROM THE DEPARTMENT OF LABOR AND INDUSTRY TO THE JUDICIAL BRANCH; PROVIDING FOR
6 SUPERVISION AND ADMINISTRATION BY THE SUPREME COURT; CREATING A WORKERS'
7 COMPENSATION COURT FUND AND PROVIDING FOR AN ANNUAL TRANSFER OF FUNDS TO THE
8 FUND; PROVIDING FOR A TRANSITION; PROVIDING FOR A ONE-TIME ELECTION FOR THE CURRENT
9 WORKERS' COMPENSATION JUDGE TO ELECT TO REMAIN IN THE JUDGE'S CURRENT RETIREMENT
10 SYSTEM; AMENDING SECTIONS 2-15-1707, 19-5-301, AND 39-71-201, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN
11 EFFECTIVE DATE.”
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
14
15 Section 1. Section 2-15-1707, MCA, is amended to read:
16 "2-15-1707. Office of workers' Workers' compensation judge -- allocation -- appointment -- term
17 -- qualifications -- salary. (1) There is the office of workers' compensation judge. The office is allocated to the
18 department of labor and industry for administrative purposes only as prescribed in 2-15-121 There is a workers'
19 compensation court. The workers' compensation court is presided over by a workers' compensation judge.
20 (2) The governor shall appoint the workers' compensation judge for a term of 6 years in the same
21 manner provided by Title 3, chapter 1, part 9, for the appointment of supreme court justices or district court
22 judges. A vacancy must be filled in the same manner as the original appointment.
23 (3) To be eligible for workers' compensation judge, a person must:
24 (a) have the qualifications necessary for district court judges found in Article VII, section 9, of the
25 Montana constitution;
26 (b) devote full time to the duties of workers' compensation judge and not engage in the private
27 practice of law.
28 (4) The workers' compensation judge is entitled to the same salary and other emoluments as that
