4 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Supervision and administration by supreme court. (1) The Montana
5 supreme court shall supervise the activities of the workers' compensation court, the workers' compensation
6 judge, and associated personnel in implementing [section 3] and this section.
7 (2) The supreme court shall pay the expenses of the workers' compensation judge and the salaries
8 and expenses of the workers' compensation judge's staff from appropriations made for that purpose.
9 (3) Salaries and expenses must be paid out of the workers' compensation court fund provided in
10 [section 3].
11 (4) As used in this section, "salaries and expenses" include but are not limited to the salaries and
12 expenses of personnel, the cost of office equipment and office space, and other necessary expenses that may
13 be incurred in the administration of [section 3] and this section.
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Workers' compensation court fund -- annual transfer of funds. (1)
16 There is a workers' compensation court fund special revenue account within the state special revenue fund
17 established in 17-2-102. The money in the account must be used solely for the purpose of administering the
18 workers' compensation court as provided in [section 2].
19 (2) By July 15 of each fiscal year, the department of labor and industry shall transfer $500,000
20 from the workers' compensation administration fund established in 39-71-201 to the workers' compensation
21 court fund.
22
